WEBVTT

1
00:01:09.208 --> 00:01:10.333
Fuck.

2
00:01:17.916 --> 00:01:19.500
We've got a problem.

3
00:01:19.583 --> 00:01:23.208
<i>Hole's disappeared. We've searched
all the places where he usually hangs out.</i>

4
00:01:23.291 --> 00:01:24.125
Okay.

5
00:01:47.041 --> 00:01:49.250
KAMPEN STUDENT HOUSE

6
00:02:24.291 --> 00:02:26.583
- Hey.
- You have to understand something.

7
00:02:27.208 --> 00:02:30.750
It's that I'm innocent.
I've never killed anyone.

8
00:02:30.833 --> 00:02:33.500
I've been smuggling.
but that's all I've done.

9
00:02:35.291 --> 00:02:37.625
You want to catch Waaler.

10
00:02:37.708 --> 00:02:41.833
I can prove that Waaler has smuggled
a lot of fucking weapons.

11
00:02:42.750 --> 00:02:46.750
I want you to find out
who's been framing me for four murders.

12
00:02:46.833 --> 00:02:49.041
You'll get everything you need
to lock up Waaler.

13
00:02:49.125 --> 00:02:51.583
Okay. We'll just do it
in a different order.

14
00:02:51.666 --> 00:02:53.541
We'll get Waaler arrested.

15
00:02:53.625 --> 00:02:56.833
When that's done. we'll have
some peace and quiet. and I'll help you.

16
00:02:58.708 --> 00:03:01.041
No one will want to help me

17
00:03:01.125 --> 00:03:04.416
now that you've caught
the fucking Bike Courier Killer.

18
00:03:04.500 --> 00:03:07.000
- But you want Waaler.
- Easy.

19
00:03:07.083 --> 00:03:09.833
And my evidence against him
is my only bargaining chip.

20
00:03:09.916 --> 00:03:12.958
Do you get that?
You have to catch the killer.

21
00:03:13.041 --> 00:03:15.416
And then I'll help you with Waaler.

22
00:03:18.791 --> 00:03:19.750
Okay?

23
00:04:31.916 --> 00:04:34.750
<i>The Czech Republic at the end of the '90s</i>

24
00:04:34.833 --> 00:04:37.833
<i>felt like a country that had just
awoken from an endless nightmare.</i>

25
00:04:37.916 --> 00:04:40.875
<i>Scared and confused.
but happy to still be alive.</i>

26
00:04:41.875 --> 00:04:44.250
<i>After the fall of Communism.
but before mass tourism.</i>

27
00:04:44.333 --> 00:04:46.666
<i>it was the land of opportunity.</i>

28
00:04:47.625 --> 00:04:50.333
<i>Back then. you could get by
on a few koruna a day.</i>

29
00:04:51.458 --> 00:04:53.666
<i>I moved to Prague in my twenties.</i>

30
00:04:53.750 --> 00:04:56.708
<i>The city was full
of booze-thirsty tourists</i>

31
00:04:56.791 --> 00:04:59.041
<i>looking for cheap whores.</i>

32
00:04:59.125 --> 00:05:00.208
<i>I looked good.</i>

33
00:05:00.291 --> 00:05:01.958
<i>I did what I had to do.</i>

34
00:05:02.666 --> 00:05:05.791
<i>I preferred women.
but I agreed to anything.</i>

35
00:05:05.875 --> 00:05:07.583
<i>You need to be flexible.</i>

36
00:05:07.666 --> 00:05:09.125
Good evening.

37
00:05:19.708 --> 00:05:22.625
<i>I realized that I couldn't
keep living like this forever.</i>

38
00:05:23.416 --> 00:05:26.583
<i>Suddenly.
an unexpected opportunity came along.</i>

39
00:05:28.958 --> 00:05:32.250
<i>The guy I'd just blown
turned out to be a smuggler.</i>

40
00:05:32.333 --> 00:05:36.583
<i>His specialty was
pentagram shaped blood diamonds</i>

41
00:05:36.666 --> 00:05:38.000
<i>from Sierra Leone.</i>

42
00:05:38.500 --> 00:05:41.041
<i>He wanted to pass along his legacy.</i>

43
00:05:41.125 --> 00:05:43.250
<i>so he was looking for a protégé.</i>

44
00:05:43.333 --> 00:05:47.625
<i>He said that my Nordic passport
and my looks were big assets.</i>

45
00:05:49.583 --> 00:05:51.333
<i>I accepted his offer.</i>

46
00:05:52.291 --> 00:05:54.083
{\an8}<i>He took me under his wing.</i>

47
00:06:12.958 --> 00:06:14.666
<i>I was pretty good at it.</i>

48
00:06:15.291 --> 00:06:16.916
<i>I was only caught once.</i>

49
00:06:19.041 --> 00:06:22.083
<i>Later. I realized that if I could get
women to fall in love with me.</i>

50
00:06:22.166 --> 00:06:25.166
<i>to send me money every once in a while
over a longer period.</i>

51
00:06:25.250 --> 00:06:27.166
<i>I'd earn just as much doing that</i>

52
00:06:27.250 --> 00:06:29.625
<i>without taking any risks whatsoever.</i>

53
00:06:29.708 --> 00:06:32.625
But two years ago.
I had to stop doing that.

54
00:06:33.666 --> 00:06:34.958
I was just smuggling.

55
00:06:35.500 --> 00:06:36.916
Oh. yeah? What happened?

56
00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:39.958
Petra.

57
00:06:42.666 --> 00:06:43.791
<i>Petra happened.</i>

58
00:06:57.125 --> 00:07:01.166
<i>Do you know what it feels like
the first time you realize you have money?</i>

59
00:07:01.250 --> 00:07:04.083
You have agency over yourself
and other people.

60
00:07:04.750 --> 00:07:07.208
<i>I was forced
to stop conning women for money.</i>

61
00:07:07.291 --> 00:07:11.750
I wanted to stop smuggling weapons too.
just doing low risk jobs with jewels.

62
00:07:12.250 --> 00:07:14.000
There's more money in weapons.

63
00:07:14.875 --> 00:07:17.041
That is when I got
in touch with the Prince.

64
00:07:18.041 --> 00:07:19.166
Good morning.

65
00:07:21.041 --> 00:07:23.541
<i>It was much later
that I realized he was a cop.</i>

66
00:07:24.541 --> 00:07:27.833
<i>As I usually did every first meeting.
I documented everything.</i>

67
00:07:27.916 --> 00:07:31.375
<i>I have someone posing as a tourist.
taking pictures of everything.</i>

68
00:07:31.458 --> 00:07:33.625
<i>and some of the pictures would be of us.</i>

69
00:07:33.708 --> 00:07:35.375
<i>So if a customer doesn't pay.</i>

70
00:07:35.458 --> 00:07:37.458
<i>they get a copy
of the pictures in the mail.</i>

71
00:07:37.541 --> 00:07:40.041
<i>a reminder.
and then it never becomes a problem.</i>

72
00:07:40.125 --> 00:07:42.875
<i>I didn't need that with the Prince.
It was smooth sailing.</i>

73
00:07:43.500 --> 00:07:44.833
He was always on time.

74
00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:48.000
Was this your only Norwegian customer?

75
00:07:48.083 --> 00:07:49.791
My only big Norwegian customer.

76
00:07:49.875 --> 00:07:52.083
<i>This spring. I got in touch with a man.</i>

77
00:07:52.166 --> 00:07:55.291
<i>He spoke Swedish. but sounded
like he'd lived in Norway for a while.</i>

78
00:07:55.375 --> 00:07:57.208
<i>He'd clearly done his research.</i>

79
00:07:57.708 --> 00:07:59.291
<i>He knew about my mother in Oslo.</i>

80
00:07:59.375 --> 00:08:02.375
<i>He knew about
the pentagram shaped blood diamonds</i>

81
00:08:02.458 --> 00:08:04.791
<i>that I'd had
as my specialty years earlier.</i>

82
00:08:05.541 --> 00:08:06.625
His name?

83
00:08:08.125 --> 00:08:09.125
I never knew.

84
00:08:11.458 --> 00:08:15.416
He knew I was doing weapons too.
so he wanted both.

85
00:08:15.500 --> 00:08:20.291
He wanted a Ceska
with a silencer and a diamond.

86
00:08:21.916 --> 00:08:25.375
And what exactly did you agree on?

87
00:08:26.500 --> 00:08:29.458
There were some very particular demands
about the delivery.

88
00:08:29.541 --> 00:08:32.416
<i>It had to be in the Frogner Park.
by the Monolith.</i>

89
00:08:32.500 --> 00:08:34.125
<i>Five in the afternoon.</i>

90
00:08:34.208 --> 00:08:36.791
<i>In the middle of rush hour.
It worked out well for me.</i>

91
00:08:36.875 --> 00:08:40.416
<i>It was easy to get there and back
without being noticed.</i>

92
00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:43.750
<i>There was no particular risk
that I'd be recognized in Oslo.</i>

93
00:08:43.833 --> 00:08:45.791
<i>I don't know that many Norwegians.</i>

94
00:08:46.375 --> 00:08:48.916
But I did fuck a Norwegian chick
in Prague once.

95
00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:50.458
She was on her honeymoon.

96
00:08:51.625 --> 00:08:53.416
But that was just work for me.

97
00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:57.833
<i>Anyway. I put the goods
in an agreed-upon trash can.</i>

98
00:08:57.916 --> 00:09:01.125
<i>The money was transferred
to my account in Switzerland in advance.</i>

99
00:09:01.208 --> 00:09:05.458
The day after the delivery. he called me.
saying he wanted another delivery.

100
00:09:05.541 --> 00:09:07.833
<i>Same place. Same procedure.</i>

101
00:09:08.375 --> 00:09:11.916
<i>The same thing happened again
three more times.</i>

102
00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:13.666
<i>Five days apart.</i>

103
00:09:13.750 --> 00:09:17.416
<i>The last time he wanted two deliveries.
One Saturday. one Sunday.</i>

104
00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:20.375
That is to say yesterday
and earlier today.

105
00:09:20.458 --> 00:09:24.833
The diamond and the gun we found in
your suitcase were for the delivery today?

106
00:09:24.916 --> 00:09:25.916
Mm.

107
00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:32.375
Hi.

108
00:09:32.875 --> 00:09:34.208
<i>Hi. it's Harry.</i>

109
00:09:34.291 --> 00:09:36.000
Hi. Harry. I'm so glad you called.

110
00:09:36.083 --> 00:09:38.250
because I've just spoken
to Maria Aminov and--

111
00:09:38.333 --> 00:09:42.375
People take lots of pictures
of tourist attractions.

112
00:09:44.166 --> 00:09:45.250
Could you help me?

113
00:09:46.458 --> 00:09:47.958
Does this mean trouble for me?

114
00:09:48.833 --> 00:09:49.958
Definitely.

115
00:09:57.333 --> 00:10:02.166
So Detective Hole took
a potential serial killer out of custody.

116
00:10:02.875 --> 00:10:05.458
and nobody knows where they are?

117
00:10:05.958 --> 00:10:10.583
We have a small
and experienced team on the case.

118
00:10:10.666 --> 00:10:11.958
Handpicked by Waaler.

119
00:10:12.041 --> 00:10:14.541
Waaler is also leading the search.

120
00:10:14.625 --> 00:10:16.958
Why haven't the uniforms been briefed?

121
00:10:17.750 --> 00:10:18.916
And the duty officers?

122
00:10:21.291 --> 00:10:24.625
We thought we'd wait
until after this meeting.

123
00:10:24.708 --> 00:10:29.000
To hear... To hear your thoughts. Ivar.

124
00:10:29.083 --> 00:10:30.291
My thoughts?

125
00:10:30.375 --> 00:10:33.833
Waaler has promised
that he can find them within 24 hours.

126
00:10:34.416 --> 00:10:37.166
So far. we have the spread
of information under control.

127
00:10:37.250 --> 00:10:41.541
It's the four of us. and Groth who works
in custody. that know he's missing.

128
00:10:41.625 --> 00:10:47.166
We have every opportunity to contain this
until Waaler and his team have...

129
00:10:48.708 --> 00:10:51.500
solved the problem for us.

130
00:10:52.375 --> 00:10:56.625
Mm-hmm. You're not saying anything.
Bjarne. What are you thinking?

131
00:10:57.500 --> 00:11:02.041
No. I honestly don't understand
what's going on here. so...

132
00:11:03.333 --> 00:11:04.750
It just doesn't add up.

133
00:11:06.458 --> 00:11:07.458
Doesn't add up?

134
00:11:11.208 --> 00:11:14.291
If it gets out that we've been
trying to contain this. then...

135
00:11:14.875 --> 00:11:16.291
We'll be crucified.

136
00:11:16.375 --> 00:11:19.541
But if it gets out
that we lost a serial killer.

137
00:11:19.625 --> 00:11:21.333
we'll be crucified then too.

138
00:11:21.916 --> 00:11:24.458
It's still possible to solve this...

139
00:11:25.291 --> 00:11:27.125
quietly.

140
00:11:27.708 --> 00:11:28.666
Waaler?

141
00:11:29.625 --> 00:11:35.250
The only way to solve this.
is for me to do this my way.

142
00:11:35.833 --> 00:11:39.333
That means keeping all of you
in this room completely out of it.

143
00:11:40.750 --> 00:11:42.333
That is very generous of you.

144
00:11:42.416 --> 00:11:46.291
but I can't accept
what I'm hearing as an offer from you.

145
00:11:46.375 --> 00:11:49.375
With all due respect.
I don't think you have a choice.

146
00:11:59.666 --> 00:12:00.666
It's 9.00 a.m.

147
00:12:02.166 --> 00:12:04.250
You have until midnight. That's 15 hours.

148
00:12:05.375 --> 00:12:07.791
The disappearance
will be released to the press.

149
00:12:07.875 --> 00:12:09.541
This meeting never took place.

150
00:12:11.916 --> 00:12:13.250
Track these numbers.

151
00:12:14.791 --> 00:12:17.625
Uh. are we tracking Harry Hole? Why?

152
00:12:17.708 --> 00:12:18.583
Why?

153
00:12:19.166 --> 00:12:20.875
- Yeah.
- Because I said so.

154
00:12:23.416 --> 00:12:26.583
Yes. good morning.
this is Beate Lønn from the Oslo Police.

155
00:12:26.666 --> 00:12:31.250
I'm calling about
your guided tours in Frogner Park.

156
00:12:34.875 --> 00:12:35.875
Ek.

157
00:12:37.250 --> 00:12:38.166
Good morning.

158
00:12:38.750 --> 00:12:41.000
- I have a message for you.
- Okay.

159
00:12:41.083 --> 00:12:45.291
If Detective Harry Hole calls you.
we want you to do the following.

160
00:12:45.375 --> 00:12:48.833
Ask him where he is. If he doesn't want
to tell you. ask him to meet you.

161
00:12:48.916 --> 00:12:53.000
Tell him that you won't publish the story
if you can't see him face to face.

162
00:12:53.083 --> 00:12:56.041
- It has to happen before midnight today.
- What story?

163
00:12:56.791 --> 00:13:01.291
He'll most likely accuse another detective
whose name I'm not at liberty to say.

164
00:13:02.541 --> 00:13:06.916
After you've spoken to him.
you'll call this number and let us know.

165
00:13:08.500 --> 00:13:09.791
Questions?

166
00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:15.708
I realize that you're police.
I'm a journalist. not a fucking...

167
00:13:15.791 --> 00:13:16.750
Ek...

168
00:13:19.666 --> 00:13:22.583
Your little brother is in cell A-107.

169
00:13:22.666 --> 00:13:25.750
Every Tuesday. he gets.
just like most other druggies up there.

170
00:13:25.833 --> 00:13:27.916
his doses smuggled in.

171
00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:30.250
He injects it and never checks the drugs.

172
00:13:30.333 --> 00:13:32.416
It's all been well so far.

173
00:13:34.791 --> 00:13:36.291
Do you get what I'm saying?

174
00:13:38.916 --> 00:13:41.625
- Why do you think Harry Hole will call me?
- He's desperate.

175
00:13:41.708 --> 00:13:44.250
And because you gave him your number

176
00:13:45.291 --> 00:13:47.250
outside the National Theater yesterday.

177
00:13:49.208 --> 00:13:50.250
Have a nice day.

178
00:13:52.916 --> 00:13:57.166
<i>If Martin Aminov was in Frogner Park
when Barbara Svendsen was killed.</i>

179
00:13:57.250 --> 00:14:00.750
he's not in any of the pictures.
and I've checked hundreds.

180
00:14:00.833 --> 00:14:02.833
Nothing that even resembles him?

181
00:14:02.916 --> 00:14:05.708
No. He's not
in any of the pictures. Harry.

182
00:14:08.500 --> 00:14:09.375
Beate.

183
00:14:09.458 --> 00:14:11.083
- Yes. wait.
- Beate. here.

184
00:14:13.666 --> 00:14:16.166
Okay. on Saturday at 5:02 p.m.

185
00:14:16.666 --> 00:14:18.916
I take it back. Guess who I'm looking at.

186
00:14:20.291 --> 00:14:21.750
Yes. does he...

187
00:14:22.666 --> 00:14:25.958
Is he holding something?
A plastic bag or something?

188
00:14:26.041 --> 00:14:29.458
I can't quite see. He's got a suitcase.

189
00:14:30.166 --> 00:14:33.375
The other hand is obscured.
I need a different angle.

190
00:14:33.458 --> 00:14:35.125
But at least Aminov was there.

191
00:14:35.958 --> 00:14:39.458
<i>But nobody was killed on Saturday.
so that's not an alibi for anything.</i>

192
00:14:40.208 --> 00:14:43.375
No. but it means that at least
some of what he's saying is true.

193
00:14:46.916 --> 00:14:47.916
Fine.

194
00:14:49.500 --> 00:14:51.750
I need your help. Aminov.

195
00:14:51.833 --> 00:14:54.125
The woman I spoke to
is risking her job to help us.

196
00:14:54.208 --> 00:14:56.708
I need something
that shows that it's worth it.

197
00:14:57.416 --> 00:14:58.458
Like what?

198
00:14:59.041 --> 00:15:01.458
She needs a picture
of you and Waaler in Prague.

199
00:15:01.541 --> 00:15:03.416
Are you slow or something?

200
00:15:03.958 --> 00:15:06.208
I can't give you my only bargaining chip.

201
00:15:06.875 --> 00:15:10.291
If I use it now. you can just put
an end to rescue mission "Aminov."

202
00:15:10.875 --> 00:15:13.916
I can put an end to that anyway.
We can't find a picture of you

203
00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:16.541
from the fountain
the day Svendsen was murdered.

204
00:15:17.125 --> 00:15:19.500
It's a little strange. don't you think?

205
00:15:19.583 --> 00:15:23.000
Seeing as the tourists have "blitz bombed"
that fountain all summer.

206
00:15:24.416 --> 00:15:27.583
At least it's bad news
for you and that story of yours.

207
00:15:27.666 --> 00:15:30.166
Is there a picture
of you and Waaler together?

208
00:15:31.875 --> 00:15:33.291
My computer in Prague.

209
00:15:33.958 --> 00:15:36.083
Good. Then you call your girlfriend

210
00:15:36.166 --> 00:15:39.708
and have her send it
to Beate Lønn in forensics.

211
00:15:40.458 --> 00:15:45.041
I want a picture of you and Tom Waaler.
and she has 45 minutes to do it.

212
00:15:45.125 --> 00:15:48.500
If not. I'll let you stay here handcuffed.

213
00:15:48.583 --> 00:15:50.750
and I'll tell Waaler
exactly where you are.

214
00:16:10.083 --> 00:16:11.625
Maybe she's showering.

215
00:16:21.916 --> 00:16:23.291
<i>Who is it?</i>

216
00:16:30.583 --> 00:16:31.583
Yes?

217
00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:51.583
Forensics. Beate Lønn.

218
00:16:52.666 --> 00:16:56.791
<i>- Hey. it's Harry. Listen...</i>
- Call me on my cell phone.

219
00:17:04.708 --> 00:17:05.583
<i>What's up?</i>

220
00:17:06.916 --> 00:17:09.208
Our hacking software is showing

221
00:17:09.291 --> 00:17:12.166
that all communication
to and from forensics

222
00:17:12.250 --> 00:17:14.000
is being monitored by a third party.

223
00:17:15.208 --> 00:17:17.666
- That's Waaler and his team.
<i>- I know.</i>

224
00:17:17.750 --> 00:17:21.833
They know you've called me.
so I can't keep helping you.

225
00:17:21.916 --> 00:17:22.791
I'm sorry.

226
00:17:22.875 --> 00:17:25.791
<i>Aminov's girlfriend
will be emailing you a picture.</i>

227
00:17:26.375 --> 00:17:30.125
<i>It shows Aminov
and Waaler meeting in Prague.</i>

228
00:17:30.208 --> 00:17:33.166
I want you to look at it
and tell me if it looks credible.

229
00:17:33.250 --> 00:17:37.666
What do you think will happen if I get
some fucking email from Prague right now?

230
00:17:38.916 --> 00:17:43.125
I need to make up an excuse as
to why you've been calling. What do I say?

231
00:17:44.291 --> 00:17:47.500
<i>You don't need to say anything
because I never called you.</i>

232
00:17:47.583 --> 00:17:50.166
What? You've already
called me three times.

233
00:17:50.250 --> 00:17:51.583
But they don't know that.

234
00:17:51.666 --> 00:17:55.625
I'm using an old cell phone
that I've swapped with a buddy of mine.

235
00:17:58.208 --> 00:18:00.708
Yeah. so you knew
that this was going to happen?

236
00:18:00.791 --> 00:18:04.541
Not that they would monitor anybody else.
but I knew they'd be tracking my phone.

237
00:18:05.125 --> 00:18:09.750
I'd like to know as little as possible.
Don't send me anything.

238
00:18:09.833 --> 00:18:10.791
Fine.

239
00:18:13.541 --> 00:18:17.583
I'm getting in the usual signals every
half hour but spread all over town.

240
00:18:17.666 --> 00:18:18.708
Yes. I can see that.

241
00:18:19.208 --> 00:18:22.791
<i>It's going here and there. and sometimes
back to where he's already been.</i>

242
00:18:22.875 --> 00:18:24.541
<i>I mean. there is no pattern.</i>

243
00:18:28.708 --> 00:18:31.708
I'm from the police.
Do you have a computer I could borrow?

244
00:18:40.666 --> 00:18:43.000
NEW MESSAGE
TO PETRA@MAILDIRECT.COM

245
00:18:50.875 --> 00:18:53.625
I've sent something
you need to take a look at.

246
00:18:53.708 --> 00:18:54.625
Okay.

247
00:18:56.958 --> 00:19:00.541
This was taken last Monday.
around 5:30 p.m..

248
00:19:00.625 --> 00:19:04.208
half an hour after Barbara Svendsen
was shot at Carl Berner.

249
00:19:04.291 --> 00:19:07.250
You can easily bike from there
to Frogner Park in half an hour.

250
00:19:07.333 --> 00:19:08.416
The bike courier.

251
00:19:08.500 --> 00:19:09.416
Maybe.

252
00:19:09.500 --> 00:19:11.666
- Are you seeing this?
- What?

253
00:19:11.750 --> 00:19:13.250
It looks like a band-aid.

254
00:19:14.333 --> 00:19:17.125
Should we be looking
for people with a band-aid on their knee?

255
00:19:17.208 --> 00:19:19.750
Or a scar. mole. tattoo.

256
00:19:20.666 --> 00:19:21.791
Something he's hiding.

257
00:19:21.875 --> 00:19:25.166
First. we need to figure out
if this could be the murderer.

258
00:19:25.250 --> 00:19:26.083
Yes.

259
00:19:26.666 --> 00:19:28.541
Yes. How the hell do we do that?

260
00:19:31.791 --> 00:19:36.166
We talk to the only man we know
who has seen the murderer up close.

261
00:19:37.541 --> 00:19:38.458
Clausen.

262
00:19:39.541 --> 00:19:40.833
Are you be done soon?

263
00:19:40.916 --> 00:19:41.750
Almost.

264
00:20:04.583 --> 00:20:06.208
<i>You think you know who it is?</i>

265
00:20:06.291 --> 00:20:09.916
It's just a theory. I don't know yet
if this is the Bike Courier Killer.

266
00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:11.625
I don't have any proof.

267
00:20:11.708 --> 00:20:13.125
It's just a theory?

268
00:20:14.083 --> 00:20:15.375
You don't know?

269
00:20:19.416 --> 00:20:21.041
<i>No. I don't know.</i>

270
00:20:21.541 --> 00:20:26.083
<i>It could be a coincidence.
I do believe in coincidences. but...</i>

271
00:20:26.625 --> 00:20:28.000
<i>Just not this one.</i>

272
00:20:30.375 --> 00:20:32.416
<i>But now. I know what I need to do.</i>

273
00:20:37.166 --> 00:20:40.250
I'm sorry. I got home late last night.

274
00:20:40.333 --> 00:20:42.291
You're bleeding.

275
00:20:46.083 --> 00:20:50.375
Yeah. Truls was a little too playful
at the cabin. so we played too much.

276
00:20:50.458 --> 00:20:51.583
Come in.

277
00:20:54.583 --> 00:20:55.583
Thank you.

278
00:20:59.291 --> 00:21:00.166
<i>Maybe.</i>

279
00:21:01.625 --> 00:21:02.458
Maybe?

280
00:21:03.041 --> 00:21:04.583
It's possible. yeah.

281
00:21:05.166 --> 00:21:09.291
He did have the same clothes
and the same helmet and sunglasses.

282
00:21:09.375 --> 00:21:10.958
And a band-aid on the knee?

283
00:21:12.041 --> 00:21:14.750
Like I said earlier today.
I'm not entirely used to

284
00:21:14.833 --> 00:21:17.416
studying men's bodies that closely.

285
00:21:17.500 --> 00:21:22.958
but if it may please you.
my immediate feeling

286
00:21:23.041 --> 00:21:25.541
is that this is the same guy that I saw.

287
00:21:25.625 --> 00:21:27.333
Apart from that...

288
00:21:31.958 --> 00:21:32.791
Maya Ek.

289
00:21:33.416 --> 00:21:36.750
<i>This is Harry Hole.
I want you to listen very carefully.</i>

290
00:21:36.833 --> 00:21:40.291
I have information
about the Bike Courier murders

291
00:21:40.375 --> 00:21:43.625
<i>and about weapons smuggling
that involves a colleague of mine.</i>

292
00:21:43.708 --> 00:21:47.750
You will get a scoop if you post it
on the front page as soon as possible.

293
00:21:49.000 --> 00:21:50.250
Where are you calling from?

294
00:21:51.500 --> 00:21:53.875
It doesn't matter where I am.

295
00:21:53.958 --> 00:21:58.166
<i>I have information proving that Martin
Aminov is not the Bike Courier Killer.</i>

296
00:21:58.250 --> 00:22:01.750
and that a high-ranking police officer is
involved in a weapons smuggling league

297
00:22:01.833 --> 00:22:03.625
that's been operating in Norway for years.

298
00:22:03.708 --> 00:22:06.833
I mean. that's amazing.

299
00:22:06.916 --> 00:22:11.041
but you do understand I can't write that
based on one phone call?

300
00:22:11.125 --> 00:22:13.416
Right. But I have proof right here.

301
00:22:13.500 --> 00:22:16.500
No serious newspaper
will print an accusation

302
00:22:16.583 --> 00:22:19.208
of a named detective
smuggling weapons

303
00:22:19.291 --> 00:22:21.500
<i>without verifying the source.</i>

304
00:22:22.916 --> 00:22:25.583
I know your voice.
so I know that this is you.

305
00:22:25.666 --> 00:22:29.208
but how am I supposed to know
that you aren't drunk or crazy?

306
00:22:30.083 --> 00:22:34.500
I get what you're saying. but if I don't
verify this properly. we can get sued.

307
00:22:34.583 --> 00:22:36.625
<i>Believe me.</i>

308
00:22:37.166 --> 00:22:40.333
<i>I want to print this.
But we need to meet first.</i>

309
00:22:40.416 --> 00:22:43.583
Fine. Schrøder at St. Hanshaugen.
five o'clock.

310
00:22:43.666 --> 00:22:45.750
You come alone. or else I bail.

311
00:22:45.833 --> 00:22:46.708
And hey...

312
00:22:47.791 --> 00:22:50.250
Not a word to a single soul. Got it?

313
00:22:56.083 --> 00:22:57.666
<i>What do you have. Skarre?</i>

314
00:22:57.750 --> 00:23:01.750
So Harry's phone is constantly
on the move and impossible to find

315
00:23:01.833 --> 00:23:06.625
but there is another cell phone
on your list that has called

316
00:23:06.708 --> 00:23:10.291
the forensics internal phone line
several times.

317
00:23:10.375 --> 00:23:11.208
<i>Okay.</i>

318
00:23:11.291 --> 00:23:15.208
It's registered to Øystein Eikeland.
He comes up as a taxi driver.

319
00:23:15.291 --> 00:23:16.250
<i>Yes. and?</i>

320
00:23:17.000 --> 00:23:18.708
There could be a connection

321
00:23:18.791 --> 00:23:22.708
between a taxi driver and a phone
travelling all over the city constantly.

322
00:23:22.791 --> 00:23:25.208
<i>Okay. got it. Keep going.</i>

323
00:23:35.125 --> 00:23:35.958
Talk to me.

324
00:23:36.666 --> 00:23:39.958
<i>Check his left knee for cuts.
wounds or moles.</i>

325
00:23:40.708 --> 00:23:41.708
Hold on.

326
00:23:42.958 --> 00:23:44.708
Let me see your left knee.

327
00:23:49.875 --> 00:23:51.500
No. there's nothing there.

328
00:23:51.583 --> 00:23:54.125
<i>- Why?</i>
- Clausen just identified the courier.

329
00:23:54.208 --> 00:23:58.041
The same man was in the picture
in the park who was also at ABC.

330
00:24:00.875 --> 00:24:01.708
What?

331
00:24:05.083 --> 00:24:06.000
Okay.

332
00:24:07.416 --> 00:24:08.458
What did he say?

333
00:24:09.875 --> 00:24:12.916
He thinks he knows who the killer is.

334
00:24:36.458 --> 00:24:37.875
Maridalsvannet. please.

335
00:24:38.416 --> 00:24:40.250
Where. exactly?

336
00:24:41.125 --> 00:24:42.708
Just drive. I'll let you know.

337
00:24:50.416 --> 00:24:53.000
- Is it okay if I turn it up?
- No.

338
00:24:54.583 --> 00:24:55.541
No...

339
00:24:56.250 --> 00:24:58.166
I hate The Doors.

340
00:25:01.791 --> 00:25:02.791
Strange.

341
00:25:04.708 --> 00:25:06.583
I mean. Doors are Doors.

342
00:25:11.625 --> 00:25:12.625
Oh. well.

343
00:25:14.208 --> 00:25:15.250
Turn it off.

344
00:25:25.958 --> 00:25:27.041
...would be great.

345
00:25:27.125 --> 00:25:28.416
You think so?

346
00:25:28.500 --> 00:25:29.708
- Of course.
- Yeah.

347
00:25:31.916 --> 00:25:32.875
Hello.

348
00:25:33.416 --> 00:25:34.541
Hi.

349
00:25:35.625 --> 00:25:37.583
Just mineral water. please.

350
00:25:54.625 --> 00:25:57.583
Yes. You can take a left up here.

351
00:26:01.500 --> 00:26:02.500
In here.

352
00:26:03.791 --> 00:26:05.625
What do you mean. into the woods?

353
00:26:08.791 --> 00:26:09.791
Up here.

354
00:26:20.916 --> 00:26:24.416
Shit. you know what... I can't do this...

355
00:26:25.958 --> 00:26:27.291
It'll ruin the undercarriage.

356
00:26:27.375 --> 00:26:30.291
Last time. I had to fork out
40.000 kroner for that shit. so...

357
00:26:32.333 --> 00:26:34.416
You know what we'll do?

358
00:26:34.500 --> 00:26:36.458
If you want. I can book you a new car.

359
00:26:36.541 --> 00:26:39.041
They can come up here
and take you further.

360
00:26:42.083 --> 00:26:44.875
Which phone will you use to call them?

361
00:26:47.166 --> 00:26:48.958
Your own or...

362
00:26:50.875 --> 00:26:52.000
Harry Hole's?

363
00:26:55.833 --> 00:27:00.833
I don't know what you're talking about.
but this trip ends here.

364
00:27:02.291 --> 00:27:03.625
I don't think so.

365
00:27:05.125 --> 00:27:06.458
Eikeland.

366
00:27:15.916 --> 00:27:18.583
It says in your records
that you're intelligent.

367
00:27:18.666 --> 00:27:22.875
so I'm guessing that you know
what it is I'm after.

368
00:27:30.541 --> 00:27:31.916
Where is Harry's phone?

369
00:27:34.458 --> 00:27:35.708
Is it in the trunk?

370
00:27:37.000 --> 00:27:38.416
Or in the glove compartment?

371
00:27:42.750 --> 00:27:44.041
Or in your pocket?

372
00:27:50.750 --> 00:27:53.416
Listen. Easy.

373
00:27:53.500 --> 00:27:56.958
We can enjoy ourselves
for as long as you'd like.

374
00:27:59.000 --> 00:28:01.041
I have all the time in the world.

375
00:28:01.125 --> 00:28:02.083
Hey.

376
00:28:03.250 --> 00:28:04.833
If you touch that alarm button...

377
00:28:06.833 --> 00:28:08.500
I'll kill you. do you get that?

378
00:28:09.458 --> 00:28:11.333
I've done it several times.

379
00:28:11.416 --> 00:28:13.500
One time. it was around here. actually.

380
00:28:14.833 --> 00:28:16.041
Where is Harry Hole?

381
00:28:17.791 --> 00:28:19.833
Last chance. Eikeland.

382
00:28:19.916 --> 00:28:22.125
Where is your little drinking buddy?

383
00:28:22.916 --> 00:28:23.916
Where is he?

384
00:28:26.125 --> 00:28:27.125
Harry.

385
00:28:37.666 --> 00:28:39.583
No...

386
00:28:40.625 --> 00:28:47.125
Open up.

387
00:28:47.708 --> 00:28:50.541
There you go. Open wide.

388
00:28:51.125 --> 00:28:52.958
Let it go all the way in.

389
00:29:00.916 --> 00:29:02.333
I'll count to five.

390
00:29:03.250 --> 00:29:04.083
One.

391
00:29:05.208 --> 00:29:06.208
Two.

392
00:29:07.916 --> 00:29:08.791
Three.

393
00:29:10.125 --> 00:29:11.166
Four.

394
00:29:15.541 --> 00:29:17.583
I don't give a shit about his phone.

395
00:29:17.666 --> 00:29:19.041
Where is Harry?

396
00:29:21.625 --> 00:29:23.625
Wait.

397
00:29:27.416 --> 00:29:28.458
He's at home.

398
00:29:30.791 --> 00:29:32.125
We've already been there.

399
00:29:32.625 --> 00:29:34.583
Try again. you idiot.

400
00:29:36.333 --> 00:29:37.583
He's in Oppsal.

401
00:29:37.666 --> 00:29:39.250
Oppsal. that's where he...

402
00:29:40.625 --> 00:29:43.125
That's where he... Where he grew up.

403
00:29:46.041 --> 00:29:47.125
Oppsal.

404
00:29:47.750 --> 00:29:51.625
We've been tracking your phone for
over four hours. so we know where it is.

405
00:29:51.708 --> 00:29:55.333
It's not in Oppsal. which means
that you just lied to me. you fucker.

406
00:29:55.416 --> 00:29:58.750
Wait!

407
00:29:58.833 --> 00:30:01.583
Hush. quiet.

408
00:30:06.250 --> 00:30:07.208
Hello.

409
00:30:10.916 --> 00:30:11.875
What?

410
00:30:13.708 --> 00:30:15.083
Schrøder at five?

411
00:30:16.625 --> 00:30:19.666
Okay. Gather as many as possible.

412
00:30:24.291 --> 00:30:25.958
Okay. Um...

413
00:30:27.333 --> 00:30:29.000
Downtown. please.

414
00:30:30.125 --> 00:30:30.958
Okay?

415
00:30:44.375 --> 00:30:46.791
Are you sure
Harry Hole hasn't been here yet?

416
00:30:47.750 --> 00:30:48.666
Absolutely.

417
00:31:20.916 --> 00:31:22.041
Hello?

418
00:31:22.125 --> 00:31:23.458
<i>No show.</i>

419
00:31:23.541 --> 00:31:24.750
What should I do?

420
00:31:25.333 --> 00:31:29.333
<i>You'll stay there until 8 p.m.
and call this number if he turns up.</i>

421
00:31:29.416 --> 00:31:31.000
<i>- We need to move on.</i>
- But. Thomas?

422
00:31:31.083 --> 00:31:34.458
<i>As long as you do as we say.
nothing will happen to your brother.</i>

423
00:31:34.958 --> 00:31:36.875
<i>None of this gets out.</i>

424
00:31:38.250 --> 00:31:40.125
No. of course not. but...

425
00:31:42.708 --> 00:31:44.500
What are you going to do to Harry?

426
00:31:44.583 --> 00:31:46.041
<i>Have a nice evening. Ek.</i>

427
00:31:47.333 --> 00:31:50.333
That makes you sure
the thing with the journalist was a trap?

428
00:31:50.416 --> 00:31:56.000
I only mentioned a police officer.
and she said detective.

429
00:31:58.458 --> 00:32:03.125
That means she knows it's Waaler.
There's only one way she figured that out.

430
00:32:03.208 --> 00:32:04.625
He's made her trick you.

431
00:32:04.708 --> 00:32:09.083
Yeah. maybe it was a mistake.
but I feel she was trying to warn me.

432
00:32:09.833 --> 00:32:12.708
Yeah. and maybe they were
tracking the conversation.

433
00:32:12.791 --> 00:32:14.291
Maybe the line was bugged.

434
00:32:14.375 --> 00:32:16.583
Do you get paranoid?

435
00:32:17.333 --> 00:32:20.208
Yeah. maybe...
But that doesn't mean that it's not...

436
00:32:20.291 --> 00:32:23.625
That they're not after you. I know.
I'm the same.

437
00:32:24.125 --> 00:32:25.875
There must be other journalists.

438
00:32:25.958 --> 00:32:27.583
None that I trust.

439
00:32:29.458 --> 00:32:32.916
Anyway. I don't think I should be
calling more from this phone.

440
00:32:33.000 --> 00:32:35.041
They'll be tracking us.

441
00:32:35.125 --> 00:32:37.083
You're definitely paranoid.

442
00:32:38.833 --> 00:32:41.041
Why would Waaler know about that phone?

443
00:32:41.875 --> 00:32:45.416
The deal I made with my taxi friend
was that he was supposed to call me

444
00:32:45.500 --> 00:32:49.791
from a call center at Grønland between
five and six if everything was okay.

445
00:32:50.708 --> 00:32:53.750
And now... it's ten past six.

446
00:32:54.416 --> 00:32:57.208
That means that they already know
about that phone.

447
00:32:58.583 --> 00:32:59.875
And they're on their way.

448
00:32:59.958 --> 00:33:03.375
In that case. I think you're doing
very little to get us out of here.

449
00:33:05.166 --> 00:33:07.291
FORENSICS

450
00:33:08.041 --> 00:33:10.291
- Beate Lønn.
<i>- Hi. this is the lab calling.</i>

451
00:33:10.875 --> 00:33:12.541
<i>Listen. it's about that seed.</i>

452
00:33:20.625 --> 00:33:22.166
Shit. is that a burner phone?

453
00:33:25.708 --> 00:33:28.666
If you've had a burner phone
in your pocket this whole time.

454
00:33:28.750 --> 00:33:32.958
why did you call from that other phone
that you knew could be tracked?

455
00:33:33.041 --> 00:33:34.250
You tell me.

456
00:33:39.166 --> 00:33:42.791
- You want him to find us.
- Yeah. Interesting theory.

457
00:33:50.708 --> 00:33:52.875
<i>- Hi.</i>
- Hi. Beate. It's Harry.

458
00:33:52.958 --> 00:33:55.083
<i>- Hi. Harry.</i>
- Have you found anything new?

459
00:33:55.166 --> 00:33:57.541
<i>I just got the results from the lab.</i>

460
00:33:57.625 --> 00:34:00.083
<i>It is the type of seed that you suspected.</i>

461
00:34:03.291 --> 00:34:06.250
- Thank you. that's exactly what I needed.
<i>- So it is him?</i>

462
00:34:07.041 --> 00:34:07.875
Yes.

463
00:34:09.125 --> 00:34:10.208
Thank you. Beate.

464
00:34:10.958 --> 00:34:11.916
You stay here.

465
00:34:39.375 --> 00:34:41.500
But what's this?

466
00:34:42.250 --> 00:34:43.208
Seeds.

467
00:34:51.875 --> 00:34:53.583
Was that Hole you were talking to?

468
00:34:54.666 --> 00:34:55.500
No.

469
00:34:55.583 --> 00:34:57.125
- No?
- No.

470
00:34:58.500 --> 00:34:59.583
No.

471
00:35:01.750 --> 00:35:02.875
Let go.

472
00:35:03.583 --> 00:35:05.041
I thought you liked this.

473
00:35:08.083 --> 00:35:09.416
What do you want?

474
00:35:10.458 --> 00:35:12.000
I want to give you a chance.

475
00:35:14.041 --> 00:35:16.291
- To do what?
- A chance to keep your job.

476
00:35:16.375 --> 00:35:19.666
I know that Hole called you
from his taxi driving buddy's phone.

477
00:35:20.916 --> 00:35:23.083
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

478
00:35:23.166 --> 00:35:24.500
- Answer me!
- I don't know!

479
00:35:26.958 --> 00:35:30.208
- Where is he?
- I don't know!

480
00:35:33.500 --> 00:35:35.750
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

481
00:35:35.833 --> 00:35:37.791
- Where is Hole?
- I don't know.

482
00:35:37.875 --> 00:35:39.750
- Don't lie.
- I said. I don't know!

483
00:35:39.833 --> 00:35:42.916
Don't lie! I'll break your arm. I swear.

484
00:35:43.000 --> 00:35:44.416
I'll break your arm. Answer me.

485
00:35:45.875 --> 00:35:47.625
Send in Holm!

486
00:35:47.708 --> 00:35:49.416
- Now!
<i>- Okay.</i>

487
00:35:53.583 --> 00:35:55.333
If you utter a word about this.

488
00:35:55.916 --> 00:35:58.083
I'll fucking kill you. Do you get that?

489
